## LibreMesh Integration

### QEMU LibreMesh Environment
- **Recommended image**: `libremesh-2020.4-ow19-x86-64` (stable, tested)
- **Network**: QEMU creates LibreMesh node at `10.13.0.1`
- **Access**: Console via `screen -r libremesh`, web at `http://10.13.0.1`
- **Prerequisites**: `../lime-packages/` directory with QEMU tools

### Real Router Configuration
- Production deployments serve from `/www/app/` via uHTTPd
- Access via `thisnode.info` or router IP address
- Real configuration manipulation through tested API endpoints
- Session-based authentication with ACL permissions

## Common Issues & Solutions

### Frontend-Only Development
Without LibreMesh backend, expect:
- `/ubus` endpoint 500 errors (normal - no router backend)
- WebSocket connection failures (hot-reload limitation)
- JSON parsing errors from API calls (HTML error pages instead of JSON)

### I18n Integration
- Ensure `i18n.activate()` called before rendering I18nProvider
- Use `lingui extract` → `lingui compile` workflow
- 24 languages supported, Spanish at 100% translation

### VS Code Integration
- F5 debugging configured with 8 launch configurations
- Integrated terminal has QEMU environment variables
- Jest test explorer enabled with coverage on load
- File nesting patterns for cleaner explorer view

